Reprieve has come the way of Ms. Attah Margaret, a nurse whose legs were amputated following terror attack at the St Francis Catholic Church, Owo, Owo local government area. The explosives thrown by the terrorists shattered her legs, which were amputated to save her life. Attah could barely muttered words when approached for interview by journalists. Her colleagues, through the National Association of Nigeria Nurses and Midwives (NANNM), have presented her with cash to help get her life back. National President, Comrade Nnachi Michael, who presented the cheque to her at the Federal Medical Centre, Owo, condemned the attack prayed for quick recovery of affected victims   Igweship throne tears Enugu community apart     APC Deputy Women Leader vows to ensure Tinubu’s…     Femi Kuti @ 60   Read Also: Owo massacre: Yorubaland can’t be conquered, says Akintoye Comrade Nnachi said the medical financial assistance to Nurse Margaret on behalf of the National leadership of NANNM was to enable her know that people care for her. Nnachi promised that the body would not abandon her. He thanked efforts of medical personel and the Nursing community in Owo for the steps taken to ensuring quick recovery of the victims. Gift items were also donated by NANNM to other affected victims in various ward of the hospital State Chairman of NANNM, Comrade Kehinde Olomiye also presented an undisclosed amount in cheque on behalf of the Ondo State Council to Margaret.